afterSOLIDrevisionEHL.model

Class ComposedElement<T extends SimpleElement>

  • java.lang.Object
    • afterSOLIDrevisionEHL.model.Element
      • afterSOLIDrevisionEHL.model.ComposedElement<T>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Requestable, java.lang.Comparable<Element>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    BookCollection, CDCollection, DVDCollection

    public abstract class ComposedElement<T extends SimpleElement>
extends Element
    Class whose instances represent collections that can be put in a shelf. Collections have a title and contain other elements (either other collections either simple elements), they occupy as many units of space in a shelf as the quantity of elements they contain. Some examples of collections are collections of books, collections of cds and collections of dvds.
    Author:
    (original) Daniel Gomes, Filipe Maia, Pedro Antunes, (revisionSOLID) Eva Gomes, Hugo Leal, Lucas Andrade

      • addElement

        public boolean addElement(T element)
        Adds an instance of T to this collection. If added, we will say that this contains element.

        The instance element will not be added to this if:

        • it is null;
        • it was previously added to a collection;
        • it was previously added to a shelf;
        • this is in a shelf or
        • this already contains an instance that equals element.

        Parameters:
        element - The element to be added to this.
        Returns:
        true if the element was successfully added;
        false if the element was not added.

        public void setAvailability(boolean b)

        Also, as this is a collection, the availability status of all the elements contained in this is changed to be the same as this.

      • getSize

        public int getSize()
        Returns the number of elements that this collection has.

        If this contains simple elements and collections, its number of elements is the sum of the number of simple elements contained with the number of elements contained in all the collections contained in this.
        E.g. if this contains 2 simple elements and a collection that has 3 simple elements, then this has size 5.

        Specified by:
        getSize in class Element
        Returns:
        The number of elements that this collection has.

      • isOrContainsElementsWithTheSameTypeAndTitleAs

        public Element isOrContainsElementsWithTheSameTypeAndTitleAs(Element element)
        Checks whether this is or contains an element with the same type and title as element.

        First, it checks if this has the same runtime type and the same title as element; returns this if so. If not, it is checked whether any of the elements contained in this is or contains an element with the same type and title as element. This happens recursively (since every collection may contain other collections) and if an element with the same runtime type and title as element is found, it is returned.

        Specified by:
        isOrContainsElementsWithTheSameTypeAndTitleAs in class Element
        Parameters:
        element - The instance of Element with which to compare the type and the title.
        Returns:
        this if this has the same runtime type and the same title as element;
        the first element that is contained in this and has the same runtime type and the same title as element, if founded;
        null if the collection is not and does not contain an element with the same runtime type and the same title as element.

      • isOrContains

        public Element isOrContains(Element element)
        Checks whether this is or contains an element that equals element.

        First, it checks if this.equals(element); returns this if so. If not, it is checked whether any of the elements contained in this is or contains an element than equals element. This happens recursively (since every collection may contain other collections) and if an element that equals element is found, it is returned.

        Specified by:
        isOrContains in class Element
        Parameters:
        element - The instance of Element with which to compare.
        Returns:
        this if this.equals(element);
        the first element that is contained in this and equals element, if founded;
        null if the collection is not and does not contain an element that equals element.
